# ClientLedger Core

ClientLedger tracks client time, entertainment expenses, and closed revenue.

**Stack (do not deviate):** Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Supabase (auth + db + storage), Vercel, npm.

## Import boundaries

- Supabase: `@/lib/supabase.ts` (browser) or `@/lib/supabase-server.ts` (server)
- Admin / storage service ops: `@/lib/supabase-admin.ts` (service role)
- Database: `@/lib/db/*` only — no raw Supabase queries in components or pages
- Reports: `@/lib/reports.ts` for period rollups and formatting
- Env vars: `@/lib/env.ts` only — never `process.env` elsewhere

## General rules

- TypeScript everywhere; no plain JavaScript
- App Router only (`app/`, not `pages/`)
- Functional components with hooks; no class components
- Tailwind only — no CSS modules or styled-components
- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or URLs
- Prefer server components; use client components only when interactivity is required

## Product north star

Users log client touchpoints (lunch, dinner, golf, meetings) with optional expenses and deal value, then review quarterly and yearly ROI by client.
